  "prompt": "Where is travencore state in India?",
  "response": "Travancore was a princely state in the southwestern part of India during the British Raj. It largely encompassed what are now the southern part of Kerala and a small portion of Tamil Nadu. After India gained independence in 1947, Travancore became part of the Indian Union, eventually merging with the Cochin state to form the state of Travancore-Cochin. In 1956, with the States Reorganisation Act, it was integrated into the newly formed state of Kerala. Therefore, Travancore as a separate political entity no longer exists, but its historical region is now a part of Kerala.",
